-- Greece’s Metka Wins $155 Million Jordan Power Plant Contract
-- B y   M o h a m m a d   T a y s e e r
-- 2012-09-24T14:48:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/greece-s-metka-wins-155-million-jordan-power-plant-contract.html
Metka SA (METTK)  won a $155 million
contract to increase the capacity of Samra Electric Power Co.’s
plant in Jordan by 143 megawatts, Petra reported.  The upgrade will be carried out within 28 months and will
bring the gas-fed station’s total generation capacity to 1,050
megawatts, the official news agency reported, citing Amjad
Rawashdeh, the plant’s director general. The project is financed
by several Arab funds, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mohammad Tayseer in Amman at 
 mtayseer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
